}) 13. O-O Nd7 14. g6 Nhf6 {Black tries to close the lines around his King. In
the Sicilian, Black's King may stay in the center of the board, instead of the
short castling. Thus, more important than to castle is to protect the King
with the pieces. This strategy is a very risky one. On the other hand, White
pieces are very active here and he manages to play g6. The move g6 is the most
critical attacking move which can create a lot of problems for the Black's
King.} 15. c3 Ne5 (15... Qe7 $5 {This is a very interesting alternative. Queen
